macOS
set background=dark
colorscheme default

Otherwise, the terminal can still auto-detect through its settings.


Windows
Designed for C/C++ Support
Include the following lines to your .vimrc:

highlight Normal ctermbg=black ctermfg=white guibg=#202020 guifg=white
highlight Comment ctermfg=cyan guifg=cyan
highlight Statement ctermfg=yellow guifg=yellow
highlight Type ctermfg=green guifg=green
highlight Include ctermfg=cyan guifg=cyan
highlight Constant ctermfg=magenta guifg=magenta
highlight LineNr ctermfg=yellow guifg=yellow
highlight CursorLineNr ctermfg=yellow guifg=yellow
highlight EndOfBuffer ctermfg=lightmagenta guifg=lightmagenta
highlight SpecialChar ctermfg=lightred guifg=lightred

colorscheme is default, but does not need to be included
cterm = Windows Terminal
gui = gVim (GUI)

Note: This is roughly an estimate of the colors on macOS.
